name: 4-(cytidine 5'-diphospho)-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol kinase
classes: Phosphotransferases with an alcohol group as acceptor
comment: The enzyme from Escherichia coli requires Mg2+ or Mn2+. Forms part of an alternative nonmevalonate pathway for terpenoid biosynthesis (for diagram, click here).

references.title: Biosynthesis of terpenoids: YchB protein of Escherichia coli phosphorylates the 2-hydroxy group of 4-diphosphocytidyl-2C-methyl-D-erythritol.
references.journal: Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U. S. A. 97 (2000) 1062-7.

references.title: Studies on the nonmevalonate pathway: conversion of 4-(cytidine 5'-diphospho)-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol to its 2-phospho derivative by 4-(cytidine 5'-diphospho)-2-C-methyl-D-erythritol kinase.
